{
  "id": "019d3328-6058-7163-9035-b41fc5a35d4d",
  "content": "# Claude Code Credential Mounting Requires Two Files (2026-03-28)\n\n## Finding\nMounting `~/.claude` into a devcontainer does NOT propagate Claude Code authentication unless BOTH files exist:\n\n1. `~/.claude/.credentials.json` -- OAuth tokens (usually present)\n2. `~/.claude/.claude.json` -- account metadata and onboarding state (often missing)\n\nWithout `.claude.json`, Claude Code treats the container as a fresh install and forces the interactive login flow, even with valid OAuth tokens in `.credentials.json`.\n\n## Fix\nLogin once on the host machine (outside any container) to generate `.claude.json`. Then the bind mount in devcontainer.json propagates both files and skips the login prompt.\n\nFor spoke containers, mount both files read-only:\n```yaml\nvolumes:\n  - ~/.claude/.credentials.json:/root/.claude/.credentials.json:ro\n  - ~/.claude/.claude.json:/root/.claude/.claude.json:ro\n```\n\n## Impact\nThis resolves the repeated login issue across all devcontainers in the multi-spoke workspace design. Verified that `.claude.json` does not exist in the current devcontainer at `/root/.claude/`.",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
